subSubSection.paragraph:
As expected, the present study shows that the Raouliidae and Typhlocarcinodidae (as well as Caecopilumnidae ) are not distinct familes (see also
Guinot et al. 2013: 113
) and are not related to Chasmocarcinidae . They are instead junior subjective synonyms of Acidopsidae .

